{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make public inquiry recommendations legally enforceable",
        "additional_details": "As a survivor and former member of IICSA\u2019s Victims and Survivors Consultative Panel, I saw the cost of truth without action. We think inquiries like IICSA, Grenfell, the Post Office and Infected Blood gave survivors truth \u2014 but not justice. Ignored recommendations can retraumatise and allow harm to repeat. Children are being sexually abused and exploited. This must stop. Child protection is a duty of care we all need to meet.",
        "background": "Amend the Inquiries Act 2005 to:\r\n\u2013 Require formal government responses to inquiry recommendations within 12 months\r\n\u2013 Legally mandate implementation plans\r\n\u2013 Establish independent oversight to monitor progress and ensure meaningful accountability",
